<div id="review_2506466179" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2506466179" />
    <a title="Don" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15211446-don"><img alt="Don" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2506466179?book_show_action=true">Aug 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Don" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Don" href="/user/show/15211446-don">Don</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2506466179" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15946157667190838112">If you&apos;re thinking of going to Africa and curious about where not to go, you owe it to yourself to pick up a few tips from Tim Butcher. In Blood River he follows in the footsteps of Henry Morton Stanley in his trek through the Congo. This time he&apos;s traipsing through Liberia and Sierra Leone, following the journey of Graham Greene. Butcher has a keen eye, and his observations, both historical and present-day are fascinating, educational and entertaining, and occasionally horrifying. If you&apos;ve any</span>
  <span id="freeText15946157667190838112" style="display:none">If you're thinking of going to Africa and curious about where not to go, you owe it to yourself to pick up a few tips from Tim Butcher. In Blood River he follows in the footsteps of Henry Morton Stanley in his trek through the Congo. This time he's traipsing through Liberia and Sierra Leone, following the journey of Graham Greene. Butcher has a keen eye, and his observations, both historical and present-day are fascinating, educational and entertaining, and occasionally horrifying. If you've any curiosity as to why Africa is often referred to as the Dark Continent this is another fine read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15946157667190838112" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


