<div id="review_2150184698" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2150184698" />
    <a title="Sally Irvine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52456073-sally-irvine"><img alt="Sally Irvine" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2150184698?book_show_action=true">Oct 11, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sally Irvine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sally Irvine" href="/user/show/52456073-sally-irvine">Sally Irvine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2150184698" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11260338779438998406">This is the third of Tim Butchers book I have read and thoroughly enjoyed. This time he takes Graham Greene’s journey thru Sierra Levine and Liberia the 1930’s as his framework for another fascinating journey. I continue to love the style and structure, combining travelogue, political commentary, history and story telling. Beautifully written. Hope there is more to come!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


